column5: My friend landed this guy while we were out on Sunday. At first we thought it was a small salmon. It took him way down river.      Loving October!
Awesome Fish man, I havent been able to get a Brown yet this year, I am hoping for one soon!
Handsome fish   like the old school spinning reel too, classic on the rivers.
Beauty brownie!!!!!  Love when they get those colours, but, aren't getting that "grotesque" look that some of the males get.
You have made many people here jealous. Add me to that list.  Beauty brown indeed
Gorgeous fish!!!
That is one pretty Brown!
Awesome brown homay!!  Dan is a machine eh?!?!  cheers HD
That's a beauty fish man!  Congrats and thanks for sharing!
Very nice fish!!!!! Love the reel, ya can't beat the whiskers!! R
nice big brown there for sure.  gives me hope, haha
Beauty fish Laszlo
Awesome looking brown Thanks for sharing Lasz!!! Leechman
Nice fish Laszlo !!  Congrats to your buddy.
Grats on that sweet lookin brown. I got my first brown this morning on a black stone fly nymph, but it was nowhere as nice at this one.
What a handsome trout.  Thanks for sharing this.
Very nice! Biggest brown I've seen this fall so far!
Thats a pretty brown for sure .., and I too love those Diawa Whiskers ... best drag on the market IMHO ( I own several )
That is a great looking a sizeable brown! Wondering if that is resident or caught in lower river by big lake?
Cleo in a river? Beauty Brownie
Guess number 2.
That's a really nice Brown trout... do Browns die after they spawn?
